00:19:15,960 --> 00:19:19,342
[SPEAKER_17]: So that also lets you know that if you see yes, it is allowed.

174
00:19:19,723 --> 00:19:24,786
[SPEAKER_17]: If you see no, allowed as of right or with site plan review depending on the intensity.

175
00:19:25,187 --> 00:19:27,608
[SPEAKER_17]: If it's no, it's not allowed or in.

176
00:19:28,089 --> 00:19:31,792
[SPEAKER_17]: And if it's CDB, it's a special permit by the Community Development Board.

177
00:19:33,113 --> 00:19:42,725
[SPEAKER_17]: Some other examples of the differentiation among uses for these three districts, banks and financial institutions, for example, our Community Development Board special permits.

178
00:19:43,225 --> 00:19:48,953
[SPEAKER_17]: This is because we are trying to follow the comprehensive plan.

179
00:19:50,274 --> 00:19:53,817
[SPEAKER_17]: and really promote that walkable mixed-use environment there.

180
00:19:54,197 --> 00:19:59,702
[SPEAKER_17]: You'll see that medical office and clinics, also community development board in one and two.

181
00:20:00,603 --> 00:20:04,726
[SPEAKER_17]: Drive-through retail sales and customer service, you'll see the footnote there.

182
00:20:05,287 --> 00:20:10,772
[SPEAKER_17]: We are examining the idea of allowing a drive-through pharmacy with standards.

183
00:20:11,152 --> 00:20:14,315
[SPEAKER_17]: I'm going to show you what those standards are later in the presentation.

184
00:20:14,795 --> 00:20:24,001
[SPEAKER_17]: However, you can see eating places with drive-throughs are not allowed, and a retail that is not pharmacy is also not allowed.

185
00:20:25,642 --> 00:20:28,764
[SPEAKER_17]: A couple of industrial uses allowing for printing and publishing.

186
00:20:28,804 --> 00:20:39,631
[SPEAKER_17]: This is near a university after all and research testing laboratory, life science facilities in BA2 and BA3, but not in BA1 except for the research and testing laboratory.

187
00:20:41,292 --> 00:20:41,812
[SPEAKER_17]: Oh, is it?

188
