[SPEAKER_17]: I think there's, and we talked a little bit about this on Monday night, is that when we are looking at zoning, we're looking at a couple of different things.

278
00:30:24,740 --> 00:30:30,765
[SPEAKER_17]: One is what's existing now, how many non-conformities, that's why we talk ad infinitum about non-conformities.

279
00:30:31,345 --> 00:30:39,649
[SPEAKER_17]: Is there a way we can make it easier for existing property owners to invest in their properties without having to go through a variance?

280
00:30:39,749 --> 00:30:45,352
[SPEAKER_17]: So step number one, what we're doing can address those non-conformities.

281
00:30:45,592 --> 00:30:54,456
[SPEAKER_17]: And then the next thing that we're looking at is a couple of different documents primarily for this area, the Medford Comprehensive Plan.

282
00:30:55,196 --> 00:31:04,206
[SPEAKER_17]: and the Climate Action and Adaptation Plan that start to inform this idea of the walkable districts, the mixed-use districts.

283
00:31:04,266 --> 00:31:14,377
[SPEAKER_17]: I think the maps that Paola showed of the existing land uses show that these are already mixed-use districts and the existing zoning doesn't reflect that.

284
00:31:14,617 --> 00:31:16,620
[SPEAKER_17]: So the next step is how to

285
00:31:17,921 --> 00:31:18,561
[SPEAKER_17]: address that.

286
00:31:18,642 --> 00:31:31,834
[SPEAKER_17]: And then the third step is going a little bit deeper on the ground and understanding, and there's a reason that there are three separate sub-districts to your question, President Behrs, is we have one section with these smaller lots.

287
00:31:32,495 --> 00:31:39,321
[SPEAKER_17]: The type of developments that's going to likely come over time on those smaller lots is very different.

288
00:31:39,341 --> 00:31:41,083
[SPEAKER_17]: This is in the BA1 district.

289
00:31:41,603 --> 00:31:49,249
[SPEAKER_17]: from the type of development that's likely to happen in the BA3 where you have these larger lots, existing larger buildings on them.

290
00:31:49,950 --> 00:31:57,536
[SPEAKER_17]: So thinking about how zoning will support these ideas of walkable areas but lead to different results.

291
00:31:57,576 --> 00:31:59,698
[SPEAKER_17]: That's why you would have two different sub-districts.

292
00:32:00,318 --> 00:32:15,363
[SPEAKER_17]: And then Boston Avenue South, same thing, different underlying conditions where the upper part is the apartment one or commercial or residential areas because Boston Avenue South had the industrial area in it, it already had.

293
00:32:16,183 --> 00:32:34,537
[SPEAKER_17]: underlying existing conditions that over time have been shifting more to residential, but wanting to add the heights and dimensional standards that reflect what's there now, but also give that room for the incentives that would provide the public benefits.

294
00:32:35,918 --> 00:32:43,123
[SPEAKER_17]: Probably more than two sentences, but does that answer what you were looking for on that, or can we go into more detail to help?

