[SPEAKER_24]: It would help if we partner on me saying what the known landmarks are.

302
00:33:11,184 --> 00:33:12,225
[SPEAKER_17]: Yes, that would be great.

303
00:33:13,576 --> 00:33:18,663
[SPEAKER_17]: Do you want to start with BA1, hang on let me go to a place where you can actually, yes I will do that.

304
00:33:24,875 --> 00:33:34,098
[SPEAKER_24]: Mr. Chair, what I just suggested is that maybe we would partner and then I will name the known landmarks that people will say, oh, I know where that business is.

305
00:33:34,918 --> 00:33:39,560
[SPEAKER_24]: And then Emily can speak to sort of what's currently allowed and what would be allowed.

306
00:33:39,960 --> 00:33:45,422
[SPEAKER_24]: And there's actually one other thing that I highlighted on Monday that people hadn't really thought too much about.

307
00:33:46,042 --> 00:33:51,127
[SPEAKER_24]: In our current zoning, we do not have any green requirements.

308
00:33:51,567 --> 00:33:57,373
[SPEAKER_24]: We require open space, open space landscapes, but not permeable, not trees, nothing like that.

309
00:33:57,853 --> 00:34:10,225
[SPEAKER_24]: So in all of this zoning, if the, and I wanna make sure I get it right, if the project is large enough to require site plan review, it would require a green score.

310
00:34:10,845 --> 00:34:13,206
[SPEAKER_24]: And it did not require site plan review.

311
00:34:13,546 --> 00:34:28,734
[SPEAKER_24]: This zoning requires a minimum permeable surface because right now people could in fact meet the open space requirement with paved yards and planters if they wanted.

312
00:34:29,154 --> 00:34:31,455
[SPEAKER_24]: And so this would be actual permeable surface.

313
00:34:31,495 --> 00:34:35,297
[SPEAKER_24]: So I did want to flag that for people because some people have said why change it all.

314
00:34:35,717 --> 00:34:38,679
[SPEAKER_24]: And so there are some underlying things there that we think are good.

315
00:34:39,860 --> 00:34:42,062
[SPEAKER_24]: So with that, we're going to share screen.

