1810
02:48:12,707 --> 02:48:13,408
[SPEAKER_15]: I love you much.

1811
02:48:13,528 --> 02:48:22,718
[SPEAKER_15]: So I just want to be for everyone involved, changing the zoning and hoping for the best is not a strategy.

1812
02:48:23,812 --> 02:48:24,252
[SPEAKER_15]: Okay.

1813
02:48:25,152 --> 02:48:30,114
[SPEAKER_15]: One of the things I've heard about doing those zoning changes is that we need it for housing, right?

1814
02:48:30,654 --> 02:48:32,695
[SPEAKER_15]: And do we really have a housing issue?

1815
02:48:33,615 --> 02:48:38,577
[SPEAKER_15]: One of the questions we had answered on Monday was does zoning for height change the housing situation?

1816
02:48:38,997 --> 02:48:40,538
[SPEAKER_15]: And the answer is potentially no.

1817
02:48:42,008 --> 02:48:47,874
[SPEAKER_15]: I've looked around the city and around the state and we talked about the seaport.

1818
02:48:48,294 --> 02:48:55,300
[SPEAKER_15]: 33% of the luxury housing in Boston remains vacant because the owners don't need that money and it came from developers.

1819
02:48:56,021 --> 02:49:00,365
[SPEAKER_15]: Offices around the state remain unoccupied, so there's plenty of vacant

1820
02:49:01,487 --> 02:49:04,190
[SPEAKER_15]: potential dwelling space that's not being utilized.

1821
02:49:05,231 --> 02:49:11,397
[SPEAKER_15]: I live on the hillside and one of the things that is really important to me is the owner occupancy.

1822
02:49:12,178 --> 02:49:13,860
[SPEAKER_15]: And I think that in terms of

1823
02:49:15,435 --> 02:49:19,999
[SPEAKER_15]: That could be part of a successful strategy, owner occupancy.

1824
02:49:20,419 --> 02:49:30,027
[SPEAKER_15]: In my neighborhood in the last five years, within a two block radius, there's been one house that has been, they've been working on it for five years.

1825
02:49:30,067 --> 02:49:32,849
[SPEAKER_15]: They added an extra floor, but it remains empty.

1826
02:49:32,929 --> 02:49:33,910
[SPEAKER_15]: No one's moving in there.

1827
02:49:33,930 --> 02:49:36,953
[SPEAKER_15]: They have the building permits, but no one's moved in there in five years.

1828
02:49:37,974 --> 02:49:41,737
[SPEAKER_15]: Behind me, folks have purchased from the West Coast, have purchased the house.

1829
02:49:42,397 --> 02:49:47,480
[SPEAKER_15]: And they have family come and visit back and forth, and they let their co-workers come and visit now and again.

1830
02:49:47,920 --> 02:49:50,402
[SPEAKER_15]: But no one lives there 24-7 regularly.

1831
02:49:50,462 --> 02:49:52,103
[SPEAKER_15]: It's not a home to anyone anymore.

1832
