1959
03:00:40,890 --> 03:00:43,872
[SPEAKER_02]: My name's Narelle Marr, 39 Emory Street.

1960
03:00:44,173 --> 03:00:49,577
[SPEAKER_02]: So I'm an abutter to Hillside Hardware.

1961
03:00:49,597 --> 03:00:50,717
[SPEAKER_02]: I used to go there often.

1962
03:00:52,199 --> 03:00:55,681
[SPEAKER_02]: I guess I'm just going to reiterate what other people have said.

1963
03:00:56,362 --> 03:01:00,725
[SPEAKER_02]: The Interfaith Center, I would really not like to see that change.

1964
03:01:01,946 --> 03:01:08,931
[SPEAKER_02]: It's on the corner of our street having a five or I don't know how many, if it's four or five story building there.

1965
03:01:10,727 --> 03:01:14,848
[SPEAKER_02]: would not be welcomed by, I don't think, most of the neighbors.

1966
03:01:17,529 --> 03:01:22,890
[SPEAKER_02]: To your point, Chairman Carr, you mentioned the three family homes.

1967
03:01:23,771 --> 03:01:24,731
[SPEAKER_02]: I overlook those.

1968
03:01:25,751 --> 03:01:26,331
[SPEAKER_02]: I agree with you.

1969
03:01:26,891 --> 03:01:28,892
[SPEAKER_02]: I think they should be removed from that zoning.

1970
03:01:29,212 --> 03:01:32,653
[SPEAKER_02]: I think that it's a residential neighborhood.

1971
03:01:32,713 --> 03:01:33,653
[SPEAKER_02]: It has character.

1972
03:01:35,794 --> 03:01:40,135
[SPEAKER_02]: And to the points of the others that mentioned, you know, if you allow them to do it,

1973
03:01:41,091 --> 03:01:41,732
[SPEAKER_02]: it will happen.

1974
03:01:42,572 --> 03:01:45,355
[SPEAKER_02]: People will look at it and say, oh, I can just sell it and someone else can do it.

1975
03:01:45,455 --> 03:01:48,258
[SPEAKER_02]: So they're going to pay me extra money for my house to do it.

1976
03:01:49,043 --> 03:01:53,066
[SPEAKER_02]: And it's just going to tear apart the character of the hillside.

1977
03:01:54,387 --> 03:01:56,789
[SPEAKER_02]: So, and those are my basic points.

1978
03:01:56,849 --> 03:02:02,033
[SPEAKER_02]: I'm against the dorm as well on North Ave, on North Street.

1979
03:02:02,953 --> 03:02:03,634
[SPEAKER_07]: Thank you very much.

1980
03:02:03,654 --> 03:02:11,520
[SPEAKER_07]: All right, we're going to go next to Jeremy online.

1981
03:02:11,540 --> 03:02:13,721
[SPEAKER_07]: Let me just make sure I can get you to unmute.

1982
03:02:15,383 --> 03:02:15,963
[SPEAKER_07]: Go ahead, Jeremy.

1983
03:02:16,508 --> 03:02:16,948
[SPEAKER_01]: Hey, everyone.

1984
03:02:16,988 --> 03:02:24,610
[SPEAKER_01]: Jeremy Martin, 65 Burgett Avenue, right in the heart of the neighborhood and community impacted by these proposals.

1985
03:02:25,590 --> 03:02:27,750
[SPEAKER_01]: Thanks for all the work that's been done in the presentations.

1986
03:02:27,770 --> 03:02:34,411
[SPEAKER_01]: I want to state emphatically my support for mixed use rezoning, this effort.

1987
03:02:35,251 --> 03:02:38,532
[SPEAKER_01]: It's the outcome of a comprehensive master plan for our city.

1988
03:02:38,552 --> 03:02:42,873
[SPEAKER_01]: It was developed by a great team of experts, and it was informed by

1989
03:02:43,713 --> 03:02:45,315
[SPEAKER_01]: extensive community input.

1990
03:02:45,455 --> 03:02:47,537
[SPEAKER_01]: So this is the future of our city.

1991
03:02:47,557 --> 03:03:02,672
[SPEAKER_01]: I plan to live here a long time, and I look forward to raising my family in a community that has more neighbors, more places to shop and socialize, and better streets and sidewalks that come with new development.

1992
03:03:03,653 --> 03:03:04,654
[SPEAKER_01]: These are how cities grow.

1993
03:03:04,694 --> 03:03:06,717
[SPEAKER_01]: This is a healthy way for our city to grow.

1994
03:03:07,778 --> 03:03:13,885
[SPEAKER_01]: While there is some work to be done to get this proposal, I think just right, I think it's the right thing for our city.

1995
03:03:16,768 --> 03:03:23,856
[SPEAKER_01]: On that point, I think we are still missing an opportunity and the necessity to look at this comprehensively as a corridor.

1996
03:03:24,517 --> 03:03:30,721
[SPEAKER_01]: by excluding some blocks of residential even though some residential buildings are being included in this.

1997
03:03:31,582 --> 03:03:44,089
[SPEAKER_01]: I think that's out of alignment there and again I think it's influenced by a political negotiation that we've all heard about not by what's best for zoning and not by what's best for Medford and we need to revisit that.

1998
03:03:44,510 --> 03:03:47,171
[SPEAKER_01]: I kind of hope the mayor is listening because this needs to be

1999
03:03:48,432 --> 03:04:04,033
[SPEAKER_01]: a comprehensive look at this corridor that is most evident on this north street corner that we intersection that we keep hearing about where one part of that corner is not included and the other is as the potential for 100 foot tall building on it with all of the incentives

2000
03:04:05,854 --> 03:04:08,755
[SPEAKER_01]: It's creating tension in this conversation.

2001
03:04:10,076 --> 03:04:20,359
[SPEAKER_01]: And I do think that would be alleviated quite a bit by adopting some of Chairman Carr's recommendations for reducing the heights in BA3 zone specifically.

2002
03:04:22,710 --> 03:04:26,295
[SPEAKER_01]: There are some nitty gritty details in the proposal that I want to comment on.

2003
03:04:26,355 --> 03:04:28,218
[SPEAKER_01]: One of them is sidewalk widths.

2004
03:04:28,919 --> 03:04:31,342
[SPEAKER_01]: And I know the team will get tired of hearing me talk about this.

2005
03:04:32,163 --> 03:04:36,629
[SPEAKER_01]: The minimum should be 12 feet if we're talking about walkability and street life.

2006
03:04:37,350 --> 03:04:38,432
[SPEAKER_01]: And right now, the language

2007
03:04:39,533 --> 03:04:43,377
[SPEAKER_01]: in the zoning that's proposed provides too easy of an out.

2008
03:04:43,417 --> 03:04:48,281
[SPEAKER_01]: It sets too low of a bar for a developer to say, oh, I don't have the capacity to do what I want to do.

2009
03:04:48,321 --> 03:04:49,523
[SPEAKER_01]: I'm just going to make it eight feet.

2010
03:04:49,663 --> 03:04:50,984
[SPEAKER_01]: We need to set a higher bar than that.

2011
03:04:52,205 --> 03:04:59,272
[SPEAKER_01]: I think it should be a CDB waiver only that would allow someone to reduce sidewalks less than 12 feet in this area.

2012
03:05:00,433 --> 03:05:08,021
[SPEAKER_01]: Similarly, BA3 needs to be a 20% open space minimum, and right now it's at 10.

2013
03:05:08,061 --> 03:05:19,111
[SPEAKER_01]: 90% lot coverage on those large parcels looks like a lot of building, a huge amount of building, and not the right proportion of open space to building.

2014
03:05:19,171 --> 03:05:20,653
[SPEAKER_01]: So that needs to be reconsidered.

2015
03:05:22,045 --> 03:05:30,036
[SPEAKER_01]: And lastly, and related to one of my first comments, we're looking at this right now without any context of the institutional zone at Tufts.

2016
03:05:30,116 --> 03:05:34,002
[SPEAKER_01]: And this is another point of tension that you're hearing in these discussions and in these comments.

2017
03:05:35,485 --> 03:05:40,908
[SPEAKER_01]: the things that have gone wrong with our zoning in the past related to developments by the university.

2018
03:05:40,928 --> 03:05:48,011
[SPEAKER_01]: So I heard in the meeting on Monday that we're not even gonna look at that again now until September.

2019
03:05:48,051 --> 03:05:53,393
[SPEAKER_01]: And that's different than what I heard in the last planning and permitting committee meeting, which was that it would be developed in parallel.

2020
03:05:53,433 --> 03:05:57,135
[SPEAKER_01]: And I really think we need to be doing that, even if it's not finalized.

2021
03:05:57,235 --> 03:06:01,237
[SPEAKER_01]: We need to know what's happening between these chunks of zoning that we are looking at

2022
03:06:01,917 --> 03:06:07,322
[SPEAKER_01]: in this process so that we have the full context of the corridor.

2023
03:06:08,423 --> 03:06:11,365
[SPEAKER_01]: But I think this is going in the right direction.

2024
03:06:11,445 --> 03:06:12,306
[SPEAKER_01]: It needs some more work.

2025
03:06:12,326 --> 03:06:16,189
[SPEAKER_01]: There were a lot of great comments by the board tonight and thoughtful comments.

2026
03:06:17,210 --> 03:06:21,113
[SPEAKER_01]: And I appreciate all that you're doing and look forward to the next hearing.

2027
03:06:21,354 --> 03:06:21,574
[SPEAKER_07]: Thanks.

2028
03:06:21,894 --> 03:06:22,314
[SPEAKER_07]: Thank you, Jim.

2029
