2098
03:13:14,395 --> 03:13:19,761
[SPEAKER_18]: Having a car wash for people to go to, I also think is important for people to be able to maintain their cars.

2099
03:13:20,241 --> 03:13:26,968
[SPEAKER_18]: For many people who live in, you know, apartments or multifamily houses, it's very hard for them to be able to wash their car at home.

2100
03:13:27,889 --> 03:13:42,462
[SPEAKER_18]: The second thing I want to speak about is regarding some of the comments about, you know, industrial slash kind of like more manual labor shops slash plumbing, electrical.

2101
03:13:42,983 --> 03:13:46,686
[SPEAKER_18]: And this is regarding, you know, our city's current noise ordinances.

2102
03:13:46,826 --> 03:13:53,332
[SPEAKER_18]: So experientially, we, I live on Hicks Ave, which is adjacent, we're adjacent to the industrial section of Hicks Ave.

2103
03:13:53,832 --> 03:14:05,843
[SPEAKER_18]: And I feel the noise ordinance slash enforcement around it slash norms in general is not sufficient in this city for those who live near industrial areas where noise is being made.

2104
03:14:06,584 --> 03:14:14,711
[SPEAKER_18]: I've heard complaints from my neighbors about getting woken up from trash trucks at four in the morning, trucks that are just doing business in general.

2105
03:14:14,771 --> 03:14:15,392
[SPEAKER_18]: So I think

2106
03:14:16,192 --> 03:14:24,657
[SPEAKER_18]: Looking at this, when deciding what type of businesses you wanna bring in is gonna be an important thing to consider.

2107
03:14:24,677 --> 03:14:31,881
[SPEAKER_18]: I don't have an opinion one way or the other about whether these type of shops should be allowed, but I just wanna really caveat that.

2108
03:14:32,681 --> 03:14:42,726
[SPEAKER_18]: I think to Alicia's point, it is important to be thinking about for residents to be able to have kind of like a peaceful living existence in residential neighborhoods.

2109
03:14:44,007 --> 03:14:53,234
[SPEAKER_18]: Third, I want to just say that I agree with Doug Carr's initial presentation earlier today, just about height in general.

2110
03:14:53,254 --> 03:14:54,695
[SPEAKER_18]: I thought that was really well done.

2111
03:14:55,696 --> 03:15:00,599
[SPEAKER_18]: And then the fourth thing is there was an earlier comment about rats in general.

2112
03:15:00,679 --> 03:15:06,584
[SPEAKER_18]: While I can't speak to the rat situation in that neighborhood, I can speak to the rat situation in my neighborhood.

2113
03:15:07,044 --> 03:15:11,988
[SPEAKER_18]: And I do feel that currently the city has not been doing a good enough job

2114
03:15:12,819 --> 03:15:15,121
[SPEAKER_18]: with enforcing sanitation.

2115
03:15:15,702 --> 03:15:24,749
[SPEAKER_18]: There are many houses in my neighborhood that have overflowing trash cans at trash time, as well as lids that are cracked in half.

2116
03:15:25,030 --> 03:15:27,332
[SPEAKER_18]: And we know that that is a breeding ground for rats.

2117
03:15:27,412 --> 03:15:34,177
[SPEAKER_18]: So I think this is also an invitation as we're thinking about zoning, if there's anything that could

2118
03:15:35,540 --> 03:15:48,112
[SPEAKER_18]: you know, where residents are presenting concerns, you know, in those areas, I think it's an opportunity for our city council to also be looking at how are we enforcing sanitation in various neighborhoods of the city.

2119
03:15:48,552 --> 03:15:51,535
[SPEAKER_18]: So those are my comments and thank you for your consideration.

2120
03:15:51,555 --> 03:15:52,937
[SPEAKER_07]: Thank you, Mr. Carney, appreciate it.

2121
03:15:53,697 --> 03:15:55,299
[SPEAKER_07]: Next up is Miranda.

2122
03:15:56,340 --> 03:15:57,961
[SPEAKER_07]: Please your name and address for the record.

2123
03:15:58,242 --> 03:15:59,683
