2124
03:16:00,440 --> 03:16:01,441
[SPEAKER_28]: Hi, I'm Miranda Briseno.

2125
03:16:01,481 --> 03:16:02,842
[SPEAKER_28]: I live on 2 Taylor Street.

2126
03:16:03,202 --> 03:16:06,245
[SPEAKER_28]: I'm right off of Winthrop in the Hillside neighborhood.

2127
03:16:06,265 --> 03:16:07,586
[SPEAKER_28]: I'm a renter.

2128
03:16:07,606 --> 03:16:09,707
[SPEAKER_28]: I've been a renter the entire time I've lived in Medford.

2129
03:16:09,727 --> 03:16:17,534
[SPEAKER_28]: I'm actually in a not that unique of a situation that my house is like a one floor house surrounded by two and three families.

2130
03:16:18,154 --> 03:16:20,956
[SPEAKER_28]: And I have to deal with the shadows of those all the time.

2131
03:16:21,016 --> 03:16:23,999
[SPEAKER_28]: And it just really is the cards were dealt.

2132
03:16:24,039 --> 03:16:26,861
[SPEAKER_28]: So I really don't see an issue with the heights proposed.

2133
03:16:28,142 --> 03:16:28,602
[SPEAKER_28]: currently.

2134
03:16:28,622 --> 03:16:29,683
[SPEAKER_28]: I think it's fine.

2135
03:16:29,703 --> 03:16:32,624
[SPEAKER_28]: I think it's part of changing neighborhoods.

2136
03:16:32,745 --> 03:16:38,448
[SPEAKER_28]: I don't really know what people mean by the character of a neighborhood because neighborhoods are constantly changing.

2137
03:16:38,768 --> 03:16:40,869
[SPEAKER_28]: Demographics are constantly changing.

2138
03:16:41,389 --> 03:16:45,391
[SPEAKER_28]: I love the diversity of this neighborhood and I hope to see it continue to grow to be diverse.

2139
03:16:46,132 --> 03:16:51,515
[SPEAKER_28]: I want to echo Jeremy's comments on the sidewalk with I know that there's a lot of

2140
03:16:54,171 --> 03:16:56,212
[SPEAKER_28]: potential for developers to try and get out of that.

2141
03:16:56,272 --> 03:17:05,378
[SPEAKER_28]: So I really appreciate the comment on making sure that there's enough width on the sidewalks to accommodate everyone and to really encourage more walking, biking and rolling.

2142
03:17:06,858 --> 03:17:09,940
[SPEAKER_28]: I also want to say someone who lives in the neighborhood uses the Green Line every day.

2143
03:17:09,960 --> 03:17:13,902
[SPEAKER_28]: I don't have an issue with the dorm on Boston Ave.

2144
03:17:14,063 --> 03:17:14,543
[SPEAKER_28]: I think it's

2145
03:17:15,473 --> 03:17:20,557
[SPEAKER_28]: just the same height as the parking garage is right next to it.

2146
03:17:20,577 --> 03:17:23,239
[SPEAKER_28]: And I would have rather had that parking garage be a dorm as well.

2147
03:17:23,780 --> 03:17:42,855
[SPEAKER_28]: As a renter, this whole time I've lived here, I look forward to the opportunity to potentially getting access to more of a housing stock in this neighborhood, a neighborhood that I love and wanna be in because now tough students will be hopefully in those dorms and not competing for rental property in and all around the neighborhood.

2148
03:17:43,516 --> 03:17:44,697
[SPEAKER_28]: And that's all for now, thank you.

2149
03:17:47,347 --> 03:17:49,108
[SPEAKER_07]: Thank you very much, Miranda, appreciate it.

2150
03:17:49,128 --> 03:17:54,569
[SPEAKER_07]: We're going to go next to Zachary.

2151
03:17:55,790 --> 03:17:59,551
[SPEAKER_07]: Zachary, could you unmute yourself and name and address for the record, please?

2152
03:18:00,311 --> 03:18:10,895
[SPEAKER_32]: Zachary Church, I'm on the street and while I'm not the resident of the neighborhood here, Boston Abbey is my primary commute route to and from my office that is in the suburbs out beyond I-95.

2153
03:18:12,887 --> 03:18:21,134
[SPEAKER_32]: Um, there are a couple of things that I wanted to bring to attention that there were comments about grass and tree cover that some of the other residents in the neighborhood brought up.

2154
03:18:21,214 --> 03:18:28,440
[SPEAKER_32]: And the comprehensive plan, um, does actually call for, um, you know, an increase in the canopy.

2155
03:18:28,480 --> 03:18:38,588
[SPEAKER_32]: We've had these studied for the city when you're erecting tall structures that are casting shadows over a particularly narrow roadway where boss, including Boston out that has also been found through the.

2156
03:18:39,807 --> 03:18:46,369
[SPEAKER_32]: The comprehensive Boston Avenue planning study, we'll look at the preliminary data that that's being done in partnership with Tufts, and we'll continue to run through this year.

2157
03:18:46,949 --> 03:18:52,231
[SPEAKER_32]: Feedback that's already come back has already highlighted the lack of tree canopy, the narrowing, the deteriorating sidewalks.

2158
03:18:52,951 --> 03:19:04,874
[SPEAKER_32]: And per AASHTO and MBTC regulations for road design width and standards, the way the buildings and lots are currently designated along that road, there's not a lot of room to play with the width there to be able to overcome that.

2159
03:19:04,914 --> 03:19:08,015
[SPEAKER_32]: And if you're going to build buildings that are six and eight stories,

2160
03:19:08,482 --> 03:19:16,145
[SPEAKER_32]: casting shadows over the roadway, you're not going to be really doing much to support a vibrant and replaced tree canopy along that road.

2161
03:19:16,205 --> 03:19:22,148
[SPEAKER_32]: This actually came up in the discussion regarding the top storm back during the last session of the CD board.

2162
03:19:22,808 --> 03:19:32,252
[SPEAKER_32]: At the same time, when you're discussing taller buildings on the railroad track side, leaning into the conversation that the comments from one of the members of the CD board about reconciling

2163
03:19:33,037 --> 03:19:42,385
[SPEAKER_32]: um, allowed businesses with the, um, with city's regulations, I believe it was in relation to the marijuana, um, you know, shop use case.

2164
03:19:42,465 --> 03:19:47,990
[SPEAKER_32]: We also should be making sure that we're passing zoning for buildings that are actually feasible on these sites.

2165
03:19:48,670 --> 03:19:59,119
[SPEAKER_32]: Since the, um, the trench for the MBTA was widened to accommodate the green line coming into one of the Southern nodes in one, uh, one and two of the Boston abs split zones.

2166
03:19:59,942 --> 03:20:06,866
[SPEAKER_32]: Um, we also should be making sure that we're examining the required setbacks from that, um, train trench for allowable construction.

2167
03:20:07,487 --> 03:20:09,988
[SPEAKER_32]: And that is not a site plan issue.

2168
03:20:10,549 --> 03:20:19,094
[SPEAKER_32]: That is actually a zoning issue for height maximums, because you don't want to be advertising buildings as allowed on those sites that actually feasibly can't be built.

2169
03:20:19,574 --> 03:20:25,478
[SPEAKER_32]: There will be blasting and digging restrictions to put foundations deep enough in there to support those buildings.

2170
03:20:26,098 --> 03:20:29,100
[SPEAKER_32]: The last consideration also is in relation to fire and public safety.

2171
03:20:29,846 --> 03:20:43,999
[SPEAKER_32]: that when you're turning a narrow street into a construction zone, which this will do because developers will move in particularly on the commercial properties, you have to make sure that for any road closures that the surrounding infrastructure can handle it.

2172
03:20:44,019 --> 03:20:53,447
[SPEAKER_32]: We've heard from many neighbors tonight about road overflow on existing traffic flows, the backups on Boston Ave at key nodal points that happen to be particularly narrow.

2173
03:20:54,220 --> 03:21:03,623
[SPEAKER_32]: And if we're over-densifying and supporting the construction of taller buildings that will require more advanced construction techniques, we've got to be really sensitive to what actually can be accommodated there.

2174
03:21:05,144 --> 03:21:14,087
[SPEAKER_32]: In addition, on the dorm side, you've also have to consider the feasibility of the fire safety requirements within the building code for that area.

2175
03:21:14,827 --> 03:21:15,287
[SPEAKER_32]: I agree.

2176
03:21:15,347 --> 03:21:20,869
[SPEAKER_32]: I understand that private dorms can serve as a tax revenue generation opportunity for Tufts overflow.

2177
03:21:21,252 --> 03:21:24,014
[SPEAKER_32]: where they wouldn't pay that to us if it was a public building.

2178
03:21:24,815 --> 03:21:39,247
[SPEAKER_32]: But there's also restrictions around if Tufts is gonna be the primary beneficiary of a publicly legislated opportunity of a private dormitory, that their institutional zoning plan has to be complete before we consider that.

2179
03:21:40,929 --> 03:21:48,455
[SPEAKER_32]: So just there are a couple of things in here, some of which I've already written in memo to the CD board that are happening on a board of here that have to be accounted for.

2180
03:21:48,475 --> 03:21:49,236
[SPEAKER_32]: Thank you.

2181
03:21:49,990 --> 03:21:51,431
[SPEAKER_07]: Thank you, Mr. Sertak, appreciate it.

2182
03:21:51,651 --> 03:21:53,432
[SPEAKER_07]: I think we have one last person online.

2183
