[SPEAKER_10]: So I'm actually gonna reclose my video.

2197
03:22:47,414 --> 03:22:48,034
[SPEAKER_00]: I'll just go ahead.

2198
03:22:48,054 --> 03:22:49,495
[SPEAKER_10]: My name is Meryl Pearlson.

2199
03:22:49,715 --> 03:22:51,935
[SPEAKER_10]: I live at 97B Boston Avenue.

2200
03:22:51,955 --> 03:22:54,296
[SPEAKER_10]: I've been here 25 years.

2201
03:22:55,196 --> 03:22:57,017
[SPEAKER_10]: First of all, thanks for the time tonight.

2202
03:22:57,037 --> 03:23:06,899
[SPEAKER_10]: I want to address a couple of the specific changes regarding BA3 and then just overall concern about the level of information we're working with around these decisions.

2203
03:23:07,839 --> 03:23:09,200
[SPEAKER_10]: As I said, I live on Boston Ave.

2204
03:23:09,240 --> 03:23:10,280
[SPEAKER_10]: It's north of Route 16, but I

2205
03:23:11,520 --> 03:23:17,523
[SPEAKER_10]: I'm probably a daily traveler by car, by bike, sometimes by foot along the Boston Avenue corridor.

2206
03:23:17,543 --> 03:23:24,786
[SPEAKER_10]: I am thrilled to see more housing coming to the corridor and to welcome more people in our community, as long as we do it smart.

2207
03:23:26,007 --> 03:23:31,049
[SPEAKER_10]: For BA3, I think some of the proposed building heights are too high.

2208
03:23:31,069 --> 03:23:35,471
[SPEAKER_10]: Doug Carr said a lot of things really well that I don't wanna have to repeat.

2209
03:23:35,591 --> 03:23:36,932
[SPEAKER_10]: So I'm just gonna add a couple,

2210
03:23:37,972 --> 03:23:38,873
[SPEAKER_10]: things onto it.

2211
03:23:39,794 --> 03:23:41,575
[SPEAKER_10]: I think six stories should be the max.

2212
03:23:41,796 --> 03:23:45,659
[SPEAKER_10]: It would be consistent with what's already going to be happening at Walkling Court.

2213
03:23:46,139 --> 03:23:56,709
[SPEAKER_10]: It would align with the other BA zones which are actually closer to real high frequency transit like the Green Line as opposed to intermittent unreliable bus service and the commuter rail.

2214
03:23:58,150 --> 03:24:06,276
[SPEAKER_10]: I am concerned the neighborhood is already gonna be absorbing an influx of at least 100 new residents from Walkling Court, plus the people who provide them with support services.

2215
03:24:07,116 --> 03:24:18,684
[SPEAKER_10]: Other people have commented about the traffic backups on Boston Ave, between Route 16, the one-way streets in that entire neighborhood that direct all traffic towards Winthrop Street onto Boston Ave.

2216
03:24:19,164 --> 03:24:21,666
[SPEAKER_10]: It gets backed up for blocks and blocks.

2217
03:24:22,647 --> 03:24:26,109
[SPEAKER_10]: I also want to agree with the folks who talked about having 90% lot coverage.

2218
03:24:27,910 --> 03:24:33,192
[SPEAKER_10]: being too much that we need way more green space and the mandatory 12 feet sidewalks.

2219
03:24:34,552 --> 03:24:43,194
[SPEAKER_10]: More broadly, and I've said this at a meeting last year, I just feel like we don't have enough information to be making these really critical zoning decisions.

2220
03:24:43,254 --> 03:24:45,775
[SPEAKER_10]: We keep talking about geometry, the height of buildings,

2221
03:24:46,255 --> 03:24:47,976
[SPEAKER_10]: but not about human impact.

2222
03:24:48,757 --> 03:24:50,659
[SPEAKER_10]: We're not talking very much about traffic.

2223
03:24:50,679 --> 03:24:52,220
[SPEAKER_10]: We're not talking about sewer usage.

2224
03:24:52,260 --> 03:24:56,644
[SPEAKER_10]: We're not talking about capacity of emergency services to reach a hundred foot building.

2225
03:24:57,424 --> 03:25:01,228
[SPEAKER_10]: We're not talking about how much more the area can absorb.

2226
03:25:01,888 --> 03:25:11,651
[SPEAKER_10]: I've been told at another meeting that it's just too difficult to estimate these things, but I know that peer communities like Cambridge and Newton didn't guess when they did zoning, they had the data.

2227
03:25:12,311 --> 03:25:20,474
[SPEAKER_10]: Somerville-Worcester, they used build-out analyses, infrastructure capacity studies, traffic impact assessments during major rezoning.

2228
03:25:20,534 --> 03:25:23,615
[SPEAKER_10]: If they can do mathematically sound,

2229
03:25:24,395 --> 03:25:28,439
[SPEAKER_10]: assessments of impacts about their schools, their intersections or sores.

2230
03:25:28,639 --> 03:25:32,463
[SPEAKER_10]: I don't understand why we aren't on the planning department website.

2231
03:25:32,603 --> 03:25:40,451
[SPEAKER_10]: It says that citywide traffic studies are just quote snapshots unquote and that we can rely on assessing individual site plans later.

2232
03:25:41,431 --> 03:25:44,053
[SPEAKER_10]: To me, I find this like kind of legally contradictory.

2233
03:25:44,073 --> 03:26:00,922
[SPEAKER_10]: If we are expanding our by right zoning now, and I think somebody had commented on this earlier, the council, the community board effectively legally forfeit their power to really stop or mitigate projects when our infrastructure hits a breaking point.

2234
03:26:01,423 --> 03:26:07,086
[SPEAKER_10]: So by deflecting this infrastructure accountability to future isolated project reviews,

2235
03:26:07,742 --> 03:26:12,846
[SPEAKER_10]: you know, by passing these changes now, it just seems like a failure of thoughtful planning.

2236
03:26:13,666 --> 03:26:17,849
[SPEAKER_10]: Like the state forced Medford to use data-driven compliance models for Wellington Station.

2237
03:26:17,929 --> 03:26:19,911
[SPEAKER_10]: Why isn't this council demanding

2238
03:26:20,398 --> 03:26:23,299
[SPEAKER_10]: the same mathematical rigor for these zoning changes.

2239
03:26:23,960 --> 03:26:30,523
[SPEAKER_10]: I also wanna question the math about the tax revenue is needed to make the infrastructure improvements that we need to have in the city.

2240
03:26:30,543 --> 03:26:36,866
[SPEAKER_10]: I was reading a study from Tufts Center for State Policy Analysis and Mass Municipal Association.

2241
03:26:36,886 --> 03:26:38,787
[SPEAKER_10]: I think the report came out in October.

2242
03:26:39,087 --> 03:26:42,969
[SPEAKER_10]: They documented that in Massachusetts, municipal costs inflated about three to 4% a year.

2243
03:26:44,307 --> 03:26:49,812
[SPEAKER_10]: but we know that prop two and a half caps revenue increases, tax revenue increases to two and a half.

2244
03:26:50,252 --> 03:26:55,917
[SPEAKER_10]: So the cost of serving new residents is gonna outpace any municipal tax growth annually.

2245
03:26:55,937 --> 03:26:59,861
[SPEAKER_10]: And you can just look at Natick to see that fiscal reality.

2246
03:26:59,901 --> 03:27:08,108
[SPEAKER_10]: They had lots of dense development and it's still resulted in a structural crisis forcing a big, I think it was like $7 million tax override.

2247
03:27:08,688 --> 03:27:10,430
[SPEAKER_10]: And you're also talking about things, yeah.

2248
03:27:11,296 --> 03:27:12,918
[SPEAKER_07]: Sorry, I appreciate the comments.

2249
03:27:12,978 --> 03:27:13,559
[SPEAKER_07]: I know it's late.

2250
03:27:13,579 --> 03:27:16,643
[SPEAKER_07]: We're coming up on a four hour meeting, but thank you for the comments.

2251
03:27:16,683 --> 03:27:17,084
[SPEAKER_07]: Appreciate it.

2252
03:27:17,104 --> 03:27:19,867
[SPEAKER_07]: We have one more person, Sophie R. online.

2253
03:27:19,887 --> 03:27:23,392
[SPEAKER_07]: Could you please unmute yourself and your name and address for the record, please?

2254
03:27:23,692 --> 03:27:24,574
[SPEAKER_20]: Thank you.

2255
03:27:24,914 --> 03:27:26,116
[SPEAKER_20]: Your neighborhood as well.

2256
03:27:26,548 --> 03:27:26,988
[SPEAKER_31]: Thank you.

2257
03:27:27,529 --> 03:27:28,290
[SPEAKER_31]: It's Sophie Ricks.

2258
03:27:28,350 --> 03:27:31,312
[SPEAKER_31]: I live on Cotting Street and I'm in the Hillside neighborhood.

2259
03:27:32,253 --> 03:27:40,020
[SPEAKER_31]: I wasn't planning to say anything, but I do just want to also agree with Jeremy's point about the 12-foot wide sidewalk.

2260
03:27:40,060 --> 03:27:40,901
[SPEAKER_31]: I appreciated that.

2261
03:27:42,402 --> 03:27:44,303
[SPEAKER_31]: And about more green space generally.

2262
03:27:44,324 --> 03:27:49,888
[SPEAKER_31]: I don't have a concern around six to eight stories personally.

2263
03:27:50,329 --> 03:27:50,949
[SPEAKER_31]: That corner,

2264
03:27:52,491 --> 03:27:59,596
[SPEAKER_31]: North Street in Boston right now, it is a meadow of invasive plants that like literally anything feels better than that right now.

2265
03:27:59,656 --> 03:28:00,757
[SPEAKER_31]: It's black swallow wood.

2266
03:28:00,817 --> 03:28:03,920
[SPEAKER_31]: It's, I think I saw some knotweed in there.

2267
03:28:03,980 --> 03:28:05,101
[SPEAKER_31]: There's a lot of other stuff.

2268
03:28:06,602 --> 03:28:11,266
[SPEAKER_31]: I am looking forward to any kind of commercial development that doesn't end up being a vape shop.

